<TITLE> SC 'security concerns' emerge </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 7 (bdnews24.com) - The law ministry has recommended strengthening security on the Supreme Court premises, in a letter to the home ministry. "We are not apprehending any attack, but we have recommended this as a preventive measure," law ministry Shafiq Ahmed told reporters at the Secretariat on Sunday. Ministry officials, however, told bdnews24.com that an intelligence agency had sent a written warning to the law ministry, and other relevant authorities, of a possible attack on the court premises. The law ministry sent its letter to the home ministry based on this, said the officials. bdne
